reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 16, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fantastic PSU and very affordable
reviews.reviewText: Got a different product before from corsair before buying EVGA and had to return it. Corsair was bad quality control wont even fit properly with the pins and you've to widen them with a tool . Then got this EVGA and it's great. Day and night difference. The fan was just as they say "whisper quiet" . Also has the economy mode. I use it for intense Virtual Reality Gaming computer. Very efficiently built. You wont' even see the fan turn on easily if you're in economy mode. But in regular mode even at high speeds the fan is quiet. All the power cord fits very well. Good manual. Everything nice and clean. I'm very glad I switched to this.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 27, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars What an easy to use and install power supply!
reviews.reviewText: I really liked how the power supply cables were labeled, and the ports on the power supply are well labeled, too. The instruction manual that came with it was pretty good. The only thing I would recommend is that they label the example photos in the manual to go with the numbered list of "how to" instructions. Putting little number bubbles on each photo isn't that hard. Anyway, i really had an easy time of installing and following along. And its working great. A quality product and a great experience using my new rebuilt computer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 5, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great value and quality.
reviews.reviewText: Really high quality product especially for the price. The fan is super quiet and it has an eco mode where the fan only turns on under a load. I have eco mode off and it is still much quieter than the EVGA power supply that was on my prebuilt pc. The computer sounds much quieter now. I thought it was my case fans making noise but I think it was my old power supply's fan. It is a semi modular unit meaning all the cables except the 24 pin connector to the motherboard are modular. You only have to add what you need for your pc. Speaking of cables this one comes with more than you will ever need for most pc's and enough slots on the power supply to power them all. Installed easily with no issues.I was so impressed that I ordered another 650W GQ power supply for my other pc although I didn't really need it. For an 80 plus gold rated power supply the price and quality can't be beat. The packaging is very nice as well. Comes with instructions, foam to secure and protect the psu in the box and velcro cable ties to loom the wires that you can use to manage wires inside your case as well. I believe there are 4 of the velcro cable straps. I would highly recommend this power supply. There are fully modular versions from EVGA as well. This semi modular version will give you almost the same function of the fully modular at a lower price. For me it was perfect. Throw in the 5 year warranty as a cherry on top.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 8, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Amazing Power Supply!
reviews.reviewText: I’m not sure what to look for in new PSUs, but I am loving this one! It came quick and it’s working effectively and it’s quite quiet! I had an EVGA 450w as my last one, so EVGA is making a good image of themselves to me! But there is just one warning, READ THE INSTRUCTIONS!! I put this in using my previous cables instead of the given ones, and in the instructions, in bold, it tells you to use the cables provided, I ended up frying me hard drives (1tb and 4tb drives). I was bummed out because I thought since they’re the same brand, it wouldn’t matter, but no. Luckily it was just the drives broken, but just be careful. But overall, I love it and it’s working perfectly, I recommend it!

Cant use this PSU in a protest since it's quieter than a church mouse without the nest clutter being modular. Okay, it's semi-modular but that's not a negative since ALL computers need that motherboard connector anyway. Being a Warehouse Deal I shorted out pins 4 and 5 of the motherboard connector to ensure it worked. The fan is supposed to turn, it did not. I was prepared to initiate a return then flipped the ECO switch which stops the fan from turning until the PSU heats up....Doh! Fan spun normally, and I wonder if that's why it was in the warehouse deals. I'm now a happy camper with is perfectly operating unit.

reviews.reviewTitle: Super PSU ne pas écouter Les mauvais commentaire
reviews.reviewText: Le PSU a un niveau de bruit très acceptable, il est aussi très facile d'installation pour un PSU Au design modulaire. Il possede de tres bonne performance grâce a c'est capaciteur japonais. Par ailleurs le rapport qualité-prix est tres bon, un prix tres bas pour un PSU certifier gold. De plus la livraison a été très rapide et le PSU est arriver en parfait état. Finalement, le produit est Fournier avec tous les cable necesaire et il possède également un Manuel d'instruction/installation très bien détailler pour les personne non expérimenter. En résumer, je recommande fortement ce produit et Lui donne une note de 11/10 🙂

reviews.reviewTitle: Failed after 4 months, but RMA was easy.
reviews.reviewText: This is the first EVGA power supply that I've owned that has failed. The other half dozen I have have worked for years without issues, so I won't discount this one because of a simple failure. RMA process was super simple, and upon registering the PSU on EVGA's website, I was informed that this PSU has a STAGGERING SEVEN FREAKING YEAR WARRANTY. It worked great until it failed.
